The paper deals with probabilistic models for relational data and inference, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses knowledge bases and their representation, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The use of link prediction models and latent representations of arguments and relations is also a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed model, which is relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
